modules.description: Handles TLS protocol initialization, handshake negotiation, and secure data transmission. Operates with cryptographic keys, X.509 certificates, and encrypted byte streams. Used to establish authenticated, encrypted connections between web servers and clients, ensuring data integrity during email transmission.

Provides read and write operations for TLS-encrypted data over Unix file descriptors, with support for handling system call interruptions and partial reads. Works with byte sequences and file descriptors, enabling secure communication in client and server contexts. Initializes TLS sessions from existing file descriptors or establishes new connections using a provided authenticator.
